---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Hardware & Peripherals — OpenCastor Docs"
  description="Guide to connecting cameras, LiDAR, motor controllers, and auto-detecting hardware in OpenCastor."
  ogUrl="https://opencastor.com/docs/peripherals"
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <p class="section-label reveal">Hardware</p>
    <h1 class="reveal reveal-d1">Plug-and-Play Peripherals</h1>
    <p class="reveal reveal-d2">Any USB camera, depth sensor, LiDAR, IMU, or motor controller. OpenCastor auto-detects at startup — no driver code required.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="peripherals">
    <div class="doc-section reveal">
      <h3>How auto-detection works</h3>
      <p>At startup (or when you run <code>castor scan</code>), OpenCastor scans:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>USB devices</strong> via <code>lsusb</code> (matches against VID:PID like OAK-D, RealSense, RPLiDAR, IMUs).</li>
        <li><strong>Video devices</strong> via <code>/dev/video*</code> (V4L2-compatible cameras).</li>
        <li><strong>I²C bus</strong> via <code>i2cdetect</code> (finds PCA9685, MPU-6050, VL53L0X).</li>
        <li><strong>Serial ports</strong> via <code>/dev/ttyUSB*</code> and <code>/dev/ttyACM*</code>.</li>
        <li><strong>NPU accelerators</strong> like Hailo-8 and Google Coral.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="code-block" style="margin:16px 0">
        <div class="code-header">
          <div class="code-dots"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div><span class="code-filename">Scan connected hardware</span>
        </div>
        <div class="code-body"><span class="k">castor scan</span>
          <br><br><span class="cm"># Example output:</span>
          <br><span class="s">✓ OAK-D Lite USB 03e7:2485 → camera.type: "oakd"</span>
          <br><span class="s">✓ Logitech C920 USB 046d:082d → camera.type: "usb" /dev/video0</span>
          <br><span class="s">✓ PCA9685 I²C 0x40 → driver.type: "pca9685"</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3>Auto-detect in your RCAN config</h3>
      <p>Set <code>type: "auto"</code> on any peripheral block. OpenCastor will pick the best available hardware at runtime.</p>
      <div class="code-block" style="margin:16px 0">
        <div class="code-header">
          <div class="code-dots"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div><span class="code-filename">rcan.yaml</span>
        </div>
        <div class="code-body"><span class="k">camera:</span>
          <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">type:</span> <span class="s">"auto"</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt-section" style="padding: 40px; border-radius: 16px; margin-bottom: 40px;">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">Example: Hailo-8 NPU Vision</h2>
    <p>The Hailo-8 M.2 plugs into the Raspberry Pi 5 AI Kit slot or any M.2 host. OpenCastor auto-detects the Hailo runtime and loads optimized YOLOv8 models.</p>
    <div class="code-block" style="margin-top:16px;">
      <div class="code-body">
<span class="k">camera:</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">type:</span> <span class="s">"hailo"</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">hailo_model:</span> <span class="s">"yolov8s"</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">obstacle_action:</span> <span class="s">"stop"</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="padding: 40px; background: var(--surface); border-radius: 16px;">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">Example: OAK-D Depth Camera</h2>
    <p>Provides stereo depth maps and on-device ML inference using DepthAI v3 for low-latency spatial awareness.</p>
    <div class="code-block" style="margin-top:16px;">
      <div class="code-body">
<span class="k">camera:</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">type:</span> <span class="s">"oakd"</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">depth_enabled:</span> <span class="v">true</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">spatial_detection:</span> <span class="v">true</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; margin-top:40px; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); padding-top:20px;">
    <a href="/docs/providers" class="btn btn-secondary">&larr; Providers</a>
    <a href="/docs/safety" class="btn btn-secondary">Next: Safety &rarr;</a>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
